For years, I searched for my space in this world--my "thing". In fact, y'all had front row seats 😅and while that makes me cringe, it's got me even MORE excited to take you with me on THIS journey, Friend! 

Okay so...
Remember when I co-produced my Police Department's lipsync video back in 2018?

What about that time we went viral with the Beyoncé "Sandcastles" remix 🤣🎶

Ooooh or the "You Didn't Ask, IJS" web series?!!
Talking to y'all in front of that blue wall was healing. I'll always be grateful for the way those episodes opened our hearts to real and transparent conversation. 

Friend, from "Songs I Don't Sing A Long To" to skating through my first year in Real Estate 🛼 to "Ask Bud", I have found so much passion and joy in SEEING the story in a situation and SHARING it with the world in the hopes of making it better. THAT'S my thing!

The FACT though, is that 84% of y'all had no clue I even existed before my partnership with @ErrantryStudios. (about 55k 😮) 

I had ideas, yes-- but brand goals? 🥴
Not so much. 

I was creating viral content across different platforms but was unable to sustain an audience. 

But God. 

What began as a collaboration on a project, turned into partnership. With the structure and gifts that Brandan and Errantry bring and using the systems we've honed, I've refined my own personal brand with some much needed direction and quality content and as a result, seen exponential growth in numbers and overall brand awareness.

And then came you. 

Sharing stories and moments in my life with y'all on here is such a blast and NOW I'm looking forward to doing that more IN PERSON! From the Church Fashion Show to my first @Ted talk, I can't wait to meet you!
For booking inquires, please email. 

PS. if you're a creator or business desiring to tell your OWN story better and more authentically, follow @errantrystudios and stay tuned for more of ours!

Love y'all. ♥️🌻

seven years ago, i wrote and recorded a 10-song album in the extra bedroom of my apartment. i named it, “in my feelings” because of the title track, not even realizing that that was exactly where i was.

in 2020, i took the album down. 
i rationalized that choice by saying it was because of the language or content but nah, i was just ashamed;

of young Sky, her choices and how “in her feelings” she always was.
 
and then last month, I re-listened. 

I re-listened and remembered that young Sky committed to putting her raw, honest feelings and full-heart on those composition book pages and then CHOSE to share that truth. 
 
and she deserves to be heard.

I’m sorry I didn’t see that before.

I pray this serves as a reminder to give every version of yourself grace, friend. 

Even more, I pray that as you listen to these songs, you will hear just how far God has brought me out of my feelings.
And that you will be reminded that joy really does come in the morning. 

Oh and this absolutely means NEW new music is on the way. 

love y’all.
